726782f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 79th Street
726782f-a.text:
Grannd Avenue, north side, west from 82nd Street (formerly
Worinth Avenue) to 79th Street (formerly Ankeer Street) show-
ing two views of two old houses. In the background beyond
house seen in the foreground of view No. 1 is the Seitr Park
(Washington Park) Dance Hall. Views 1 and 2 show the C.F.
Howard house (1873-1891). It lies directlv in the 79th Street
line.

726780f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 79th Street
726780f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, south side, between 79th Street and the
New York Conecting Railroad. Eucene L. Armbruster states this
house was erected in 189O by Christian Homever who sold it to
the Brooklyn Dnion Gas Co. in 1915. However it has been the
home of C. Ulrick in May 1890.
July 1923.

726781f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 79th Street
726781f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, north side, west from 79th Street. The house
seen in the foreground was a part of Washington ark. It does
not appear inn the 1929 Queens Atlas. The New York connecting
railroad extends through the site. The building in the back-
grond which was used as a dace hall is now occupied by herry
Elein and Co. Inc.
July 1923.
